Section	    Requirement	Content
Section 1	Overview	The LabLink algorithm matches candidates with labs by comparing lab-side variables from Dataset A with candidate-side variables from Dataset B. It uses matching pairs, weights, and match values to calculate a final match percentage for each lab.
Section 2	Input: Dataset A	Dataset A includes lab profile variables such as techniques, scientific fields, research aims, publication goals, career pathways, mentorship models, timeline expectations, institution type, funding source, hiree level, GPA requirement, prerequisite coursework, and prior experience requirement.
Section 2	Input: Dataset B	Dataset B includes candidate profile variables such as candidate skills, proficiency level, field interests, career goals, publication preferences, mentorship preferences, timeline preferences, compensation preferences, education level, GPA range, coursework, and research experience level.
Section 2	Matching Pair Source	The algorithm uses the B_MatchingPairs tab. Each row in B_MatchingPairs connects one Dataset A variable with one Dataset B variable.
Section 3	Scoring Formula	Total_Score = SUM(weight_i × match_i) for all rows in B_MatchingPairs.
Section 3	Weight Meaning	weight_i is the importance value assigned to each matching pair. Higher weights mean the match is more important.
Section 3	Exact Match Rule	If Dataset A variable i directly matches Dataset B variable i, then match_i = 1.
Section 3	No Match Rule	If Dataset A variable i does not match Dataset B variable i, then match_i = 0.
Section 3	Partial Match Rule	If the match is related but not exact, then match_i = 0.5. For example, a secondary interest may partially match a primary lab field.
Section 3	Penalty Rule	If there is a major mismatch, then match_i = -1. For example, if a lab requires full-time availability but the candidate is only available part-time.
Section 3	Max Score	Max_Score = SUM of all positive weights where match_i = 1.
Section 3	Match Percentage	Match Percentage = Total_Score / Max_Score × 100.
Section 4	Output	The algorithm returns a ranked list of lab matches for each candidate, sorted by match percentage from highest to lowest.
Section 4	Display Rule	The system should display the top 5 lab matches with their match percentages.
